      "type": "markdown",
      "text": "In [[computing]], __procedural generation__ is a method of creating data [[algorithm]]ically as opposed to manually, typically through a combination of human-generated assets and algorithms coupled with computer-generated randomness and processing power. In [[computer graphics]], it is commonly used to create [[texture mapping]] and [[3D models]]. In video games, it is used to automatically create large amounts of content in a game. Depending on the implementation, advantages of procedural generation can include smaller file sizes, larger amounts of content, and randomness for less predictable gameplay. Procedural generation is a branch of [[media_synthesis_(AI)]] - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Procedural_generation wikipedia]"
